{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Cartoons are basically short stories."},{"time":3000,"text":"I tried to find one that didn't have a whole lot of words."},{"time":9000,"text":"Not all of them have happy endings."},{"time":11000,"text":"So how did I get started cartooning?"},{"time":13000,"text":"I doodled a lot as a kid,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and if you spend enough time doodling,"},{"time":19000,"text":"sooner or later, something happens:"},{"time":21000,"text":"all your career options run out."},{"time":23000,"text":"So you have to make a living cartooning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"Actually, I fell in love with the ocean when I was a little boy,"},{"time":28000,"text":"when I was about eight or nine."},{"time":30000,"text":"And I was particularly fascinated with sharks."},{"time":33000,"text":"This is some of my early work."},{"time":35000,"text":"Eventually, my mom took the red crayon away,"},{"time":37000,"text":"so it was [unclear]."},{"time":39000,"text":"But I'd like to relay to you a childhood experience of mine"},{"time":42000,"text":"that really made me see the ocean differently,"},{"time":45000,"text":"and it's become the foundation of my work"},{"time":47000,"text":"because, I feel like, if in a day,"},{"time":49000,"text":"I can see the ocean differently,"},{"time":51000,"text":"then I can evoke that same kind of change in others,"},{"time":53000,"text":"especially kids."},{"time":55000,"text":"Before that day, this is how I saw the ocean."},{"time":57000,"text":"It's just a big blue surface."},{"time":59000,"text":"And this is how we've seen the ocean since the beginning of time."},{"time":62000,"text":"It's a mystery."},{"time":64000,"text":"There's been a lot of folklore"},{"time":66000,"text":"developed around the ocean,"},{"time":68000,"text":"mostly negative."},{"time":70000,"text":"And that prompted people to make maps like this,"},{"time":72000,"text":"with all kinds of wonderful detail on the land,"},{"time":75000,"text":"but when you get to the waters edge,"},{"time":77000,"text":"the ocean looks like one giant puddle of blue paint."},{"time":80000,"text":"And this is the way I saw the ocean at school --"},{"time":82000,"text":"as if to say, \"All geography and science lessons"},{"time":84000,"text":"stop at water's edge."},{"time":86000,"text":"This part's not going to be on the test.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"But that day I flew low over the islands --"},{"time":90000,"text":"it was a family trip to the Caribbean,"},{"time":92000,"text":"and I flew in a small plane low over the islands."},{"time":94000,"text":"This is what I saw. I saw hills and valleys."},{"time":98000,"text":"I saw forests and meadows."},{"time":100000,"text":"I saw grottoes and secret gardens"},{"time":102000,"text":"and places I'd love to hide as a kid,"},{"time":104000,"text":"if I could only breathe underwater."},{"time":106000,"text":"And best of all, I saw the animals."},{"time":108000,"text":"I saw a manta ray that looked as big as the plane I was flying in."},{"time":111000,"text":"And I flew over a lagoon with a shark in it,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and that was the day that my comic strip about a shark was born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"So from that day on, I was an ordinary kid"},{"time":120000,"text":"walking around on dry land,"},{"time":122000,"text":"but my head was down there, underwater."},{"time":124000,"text":"Up until that day,"},{"time":126000,"text":"these were the animals that were most common in my life."},{"time":129000,"text":"These were the ones I'd like to draw --"},{"time":132000,"text":"all variations of four legs and fur."},{"time":139000,"text":"But when you got to the ocean,"},{"time":141000,"text":"my imagination was no competition for nature."},{"time":143000,"text":"Every time I'd come up with a crazy cartoon character on the drawing board,"},{"time":146000,"text":"I'd find a critter in the ocean that was even crazier."},{"time":149000,"text":"And the differences in scale between this tiny sea dragon"},{"time":152000,"text":"and this enormous humpback whale"},{"time":154000,"text":"was like something out of a science-fiction movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157000,"text":"Whenever I talk to kids, I always like to tell them,"},{"time":159000,"text":"the biggest animal that ever lived is still alive."},{"time":162000,"text":"It's not a dinosaur; it's a whale,"},{"time":164000,"text":"animals as big as office buildings"},{"time":166000,"text":"still swimming around out there in our ocean."},{"time":168000,"text":"Speaking of dinosaurs, sharks are basically"},{"time":170000,"text":"the same fish they were 300 million years ago."},{"time":173000,"text":"So if you ever fantasize about going back in time"},{"time":175000,"text":"and seeing what a dinosaur looked like,"},{"time":177000,"text":"that's what a dinosaur looks like."},{"time":179000,"text":"So you have living dinosaurs"},{"time":181000,"text":"and space aliens,"},{"time":183000,"text":"animals that evolved in zero gravity in harsh conditions."},{"time":186000,"text":"It's just incredible; no Hollywood designer"},{"time":189000,"text":"could come up with something more interesting than that."},{"time":192000,"text":"Or this fangtooth. The particles in the water"},{"time":194000,"text":"make it look like it's floating in outer space."},{"time":196000,"text":"Could you image if we looked through the Hubble Telescope"},{"time":199000,"text":"and we saw that?"},{"time":202000,"text":"It would start a whole new space race."},{"time":204000,"text":"But instead, we stick a camera in the deep ocean,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and we see a fish, and it doesn't capture our imagination"},{"time":210000,"text":"as a society."},{"time":212000,"text":"We say to ourselves,"},{"time":214000,"text":"\"Maybe we can make fish sticks with it or something.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"So, what I'd like to do now"},{"time":220000,"text":"is try a little drawing."},{"time":223000,"text":"So, I'm going to try to draw this fangtooth here."},{"time":228000,"text":"I love to draw the deep sea fish,"},{"time":230000,"text":"because they are so ugly,"},{"time":232000,"text":"but beautiful in their own way."},{"time":246000,"text":"Maybe we can give him a little bioluminescence here --"},{"time":248000,"text":"give him a headlight,"},{"time":250000,"text":"maybe a brake light,"},{"time":253000,"text":"turn signals."},{"time":257000,"text":"But it's easy to see why these animals"},{"time":259000,"text":"make such great cartoon characters,"},{"time":261000,"text":"their shapes and sizes."},{"time":266000,"text":"So some of them actually seem to have powers"},{"time":268000,"text":"like superheroes in a comic book."},{"time":270000,"text":"For instance,"},{"time":272000,"text":"take these sea turtles."},{"time":274000,"text":"They kind of have a sixth sense"},{"time":276000,"text":"like Superman's x-ray vision."},{"time":278000,"text":"They can sense the magnetic fields of the earth."},{"time":281000,"text":"And they can use that sense"},{"time":283000,"text":"to navigate hundreds of miles of open ocean."},{"time":288000,"text":"I kind of give my turtle hands"},{"time":290000,"text":"just to make them an easier cartoon character to work with."},{"time":304000,"text":"Or take this sea cucumber."},{"time":306000,"text":"It's not an animal we draw cartoons of"},{"time":309000,"text":"or draw at all."},{"time":311000,"text":"He's like an underwater Spiderman."},{"time":313000,"text":"He shoots out these sticky webs"},{"time":316000,"text":"to entangle his enemy."},{"time":319000,"text":"Of course, sea cucumbers shoot them out their rears,"},{"time":321000,"text":"which, in my opinion, makes them much more interesting a superhero."},{"time":324000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":326000,"text":"He can't spin a web anytime; he's got to pull his pants down first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"Or the blowfish."},{"time":333000,"text":"The blowfish is like the Incredible Hulk."},{"time":335000,"text":"It can change its body"},{"time":337000,"text":"into a big, intimidating fish"},{"time":339000,"text":"in a matter of seconds."},{"time":341000,"text":"I'm going to draw this blowfish uninflated."},{"time":349000,"text":"And then I'm going to attempt"},{"time":352000,"text":"onscreen animation here."},{"time":354000,"text":"Let's see."},{"time":356000,"text":"Try and inflate it."},{"time":366000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":368000,"text":"\"You talkin' to me?\" See, he can inflate himself"},{"time":370000,"text":"when he wants to be intimidating."},{"time":373000,"text":"Or take this swordfish."},{"time":378000,"text":"Could you imagine being born with a tool for a nose?"},{"time":381000,"text":"Do you think he wakes up in the morning, looks in the mirror and says,"},{"time":383000,"text":"\"Somebody's getting stabbed today.\""},{"time":388000,"text":"Or this lionfish for instance."},{"time":391000,"text":"Imagine trying to make friends"},{"time":393000,"text":"covered with razor-sharp poisonous barbs."},{"time":396000,"text":"It's not something you want to put on your Facebook page, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"My characters are --"},{"time":411000,"text":"my lead character's a shark named Sherman."},{"time":413000,"text":"He's a great white shark."},{"time":415000,"text":"And I kind of broke the mold with Sherman."},{"time":417000,"text":"I didn't want to go with this ruthless"},{"time":420000,"text":"predator image."},{"time":422000,"text":"He's kind of just out there making a living."},{"time":424000,"text":"He's sort of a Homer Simpson with fins."},{"time":426000,"text":"And then his sidekick"},{"time":428000,"text":"is a sea turtle, as I mentioned before, named Filmore."},{"time":431000,"text":"He uses his wonderful skills at navigation"},{"time":434000,"text":"to wander the oceans, looking for a mate."},{"time":439000,"text":"And he does manage to find them,"},{"time":441000,"text":"but great navigation skills, lousy pick-up lines."},{"time":444000,"text":"He never seems"},{"time":446000,"text":"to settle on"},{"time":448000,"text":"any particular girl."},{"time":452000,"text":"I have a hermit crab named Hawthorne,"},{"time":454000,"text":"who doesn't get a lot of respect as a hermit crab,"},{"time":457000,"text":"so he kind of wishes"},{"time":459000,"text":"he were a great white shark."},{"time":470000,"text":"And then I'll introduce you to one more character,"},{"time":473000,"text":"this guy, Ernest,"},{"time":475000,"text":"who is basically a juvenile delinquent"},{"time":477000,"text":"in a fish body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481000,"text":"So with characters, you can make stories."},{"time":484000,"text":"Sometimes making a story is as easy"},{"time":486000,"text":"as putting two characters in a room"},{"time":489000,"text":"and seeing what happens."},{"time":491000,"text":"So, imagine a great white shark and a giant squid in the same bathroom."},{"time":494000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":496000,"text":"Or, sometimes I take them to places"},{"time":498000,"text":"that people have never heard of because they're underwater."},{"time":500000,"text":"For instance, I took them skiing in the Mid-Atlantic Range,"},{"time":502000,"text":"which is this range of mountains in the middle of the Atlantic."},{"time":505000,"text":"I've taken them to the Sea of Japan,"},{"time":507000,"text":"where they met giant jellyfish."},{"time":509000,"text":"I've taken them camping in the kelp forests of California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"This next one here,"},{"time":514000,"text":"I did a story on the census of marine life."},{"time":516000,"text":"And that was a lot of fun because, as most of you know,"},{"time":518000,"text":"it's a real project we've heard about."},{"time":522000,"text":"But it was a chance for me to introduce readers"},{"time":524000,"text":"to a lot of crazy undersea characters."},{"time":527000,"text":"So we start off the story with Ernest,"},{"time":529000,"text":"who volunteers as a census taker."},{"time":531000,"text":"He goes down and he meets this famous anglerfish."},{"time":535000,"text":"Then he meets the yeti crab,"},{"time":537000,"text":"the famous vampire squid -- elusive, hard to find --"},{"time":540000,"text":"and the Dumbo octopus, which looks so much like a cartoon in real life"},{"time":543000,"text":"that really didn't have to change a thing when I drew it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"I did another story on marine debris."},{"time":549000,"text":"I was speaking to a lot of my friends"},{"time":551000,"text":"in the conservation business,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and they --"},{"time":555000,"text":"I asked them, \"So what's one issue you would like everyone to know more about?\""},{"time":558000,"text":"And they said -- this one friend of mine said,"},{"time":561000,"text":"\"I've got one word for you: plastic.\""},{"time":564000,"text":"And I told him, \"Well, I need something a little sexier than that."},{"time":567000,"text":"Plastic just is not going to do it.\""},{"time":569000,"text":"We sort of worked things out."},{"time":571000,"text":"He wanted me to use words like polyvinyl chloride,"},{"time":573000,"text":"which doesn't really work in voice balloons very well."},{"time":575000,"text":"I couldn't fit them in."},{"time":577000,"text":"So what I did was I made an adventure strip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"Basically, this bottle travels a long way."},{"time":581000,"text":"What I'm trying to tell readers"},{"time":583000,"text":"is that plastic doesn't really go away;"},{"time":585000,"text":"it just continues to wash downstream."},{"time":587000,"text":"And a lot of it ends up washing into the ocean,"},{"time":590000,"text":"which is a great story if you attach a couple characters to it,"},{"time":593000,"text":"especially if they can't stand each other, like these two."},{"time":597000,"text":"So, I sent them to Boise, Idaho,"},{"time":600000,"text":"where they dropped a plastic bottle"},{"time":603000,"text":"into the Boise sewer system."},{"time":605000,"text":"And it ended up in the Boise River"},{"time":608000,"text":"and then on to the Columbia River"},{"time":610000,"text":"and then to the mouth of the Columbia"},{"time":612000,"text":"and to the Pacific Ocean"},{"time":614000,"text":"and then on to this place called the Great Pacific Garbage Patch --"},{"time":617000,"text":"which is this giant Pacific gyre in the North Pacific,"},{"time":619000,"text":"where a lot of this plastic ends up floating around --"},{"time":623000,"text":"and then back onto the lagoon."},{"time":626000,"text":"So that was basically a buddy story"},{"time":628000,"text":"with a plastic bottle following along."},{"time":631000,"text":"So a lot of people remember the plastic bottle anyway,"},{"time":634000,"text":"but we really talked about marine debris and plastic"},{"time":637000,"text":"in the course of that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"The third storyline I did about a year and a half ago"},{"time":641000,"text":"was probably my most difficult."},{"time":643000,"text":"It was on shark finning, and I felt really strongly"},{"time":645000,"text":"about this issue."},{"time":647000,"text":"And I felt like, since my main character was a shark,"},{"time":650000,"text":"the comic strip was a perfect vehicle for telling the public about this."},{"time":653000,"text":"Now, finning is the act"},{"time":655000,"text":"of taking a shark, cutting the valuable fins off"},{"time":658000,"text":"and throwing the live animal back in the water."},{"time":661000,"text":"It's cruel, it's wasteful."},{"time":663000,"text":"There's nothing funny or entertaining about it,"},{"time":665000,"text":"but I really wanted to take this issue on."},{"time":667000,"text":"I had to kill my main character, who is a shark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"We start with Sherman in a Chinese restaurant,"},{"time":672000,"text":"who gets a fortune that he's about to get caught by a trawler,"},{"time":675000,"text":"which he does."},{"time":677000,"text":"And then he dies."},{"time":679000,"text":"He gets finned, and then he gets thrown overboard."},{"time":681000,"text":"Ostensibly, he's dead now."},{"time":683000,"text":"And so I killed a character that's been in the newspaper for 15 years."},{"time":686000,"text":"So I got a lot of reader feedback on that one."},{"time":688000,"text":"Meanwhile, the other characters are talking about shark fin soup."},{"time":691000,"text":"I do three or four strips after that"},{"time":693000,"text":"where we explore the finning issue"},{"time":695000,"text":"and the shark fin soup issue."},{"time":697000,"text":"Sherman's up in shark heaven."},{"time":699000,"text":"This is what I love about comic strips, you know."},{"time":701000,"text":"You really don't have to worry about the audience suspending its sense of disbelief"},{"time":704000,"text":"because, if you start with a talking shark,"},{"time":706000,"text":"readers pretty much check their disbelief at the door."},{"time":709000,"text":"You can kind of do anything."},{"time":711000,"text":"It becomes a near-death experience for Sherman."},{"time":714000,"text":"Meanwhile, Ernest finds his fins on the internet."},{"time":716000,"text":"There was a real website based in China"},{"time":718000,"text":"that actually sold shark fins,"},{"time":720000,"text":"so I kind of exposed that."},{"time":723000,"text":"And he clicks the \"buy now\" button."},{"time":726000,"text":"And voila, next-day air, they show up,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and they surgically reattach them."},{"time":730000,"text":"I ended that series with a kind of a mail-in petition"},{"time":733000,"text":"that encouraged our National Marine Fishery Service,"},{"time":735000,"text":"to force other countries"},{"time":737000,"text":"to have a stronger stance with shark management."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":741000,"text":"Thanks."},{"time":743000,"text":"I'd like to end with a little metaphor here."},{"time":745000,"text":"I've been trying to think of a metaphor to represent Mission Blue,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and this is what I came up with."},{"time":750000,"text":"Imagine you're in an enormous room,"},{"time":752000,"text":"and it's as dark as a cave."},{"time":754000,"text":"And you can have anything in that room, anything you want,"},{"time":756000,"text":"but you can't see anything."},{"time":758000,"text":"You've been given one tool, a hammer."},{"time":761000,"text":"So you wander around in the darkness, and you bump into something,"},{"time":764000,"text":"and it feels like it's made of stone."},{"time":766000,"text":"It's big, it's heavy. You can't carry it away,"},{"time":768000,"text":"so you bang it with your hammer, and you break off a piece."},{"time":771000,"text":"And you take the piece out into the daylight."},{"time":773000,"text":"And you see you have a beautiful piece of white alabaster."},{"time":776000,"text":"So you say to yourself, \"Well, that's worth something.\""},{"time":778000,"text":"So you go back into the room,"},{"time":780000,"text":"and you break this thing to pieces, and you haul it away."},{"time":783000,"text":"And you find other things, and you break that up, and you haul those away."},{"time":785000,"text":"And you're getting all kinds of cool stuff."},{"time":787000,"text":"And you hear other people doing the same thing."},{"time":789000,"text":"So you get this sense of urgency,"},{"time":791000,"text":"like you need to find as much stuff as possible as soon as possible."},{"time":794000,"text":"And then some yells, \"Stop!\""},{"time":796000,"text":"And they turn up the lights."},{"time":798000,"text":"And you realize where you are; you're in the Louvre."},{"time":803000,"text":"And you've taken all this complexity and beauty,"},{"time":807000,"text":"and you've turned it into a cheap commodity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"And that's what we're doing with the ocean."},{"time":813000,"text":"And part of what Mission Blue is about"},{"time":815000,"text":"is yelling, \"Stop!\""},{"time":818000,"text":"so that each of us --"},{"time":820000,"text":"explorer, scientist, cartoonist, singer, chef --"},{"time":823000,"text":"can turn up the lights in their own way."},{"time":825000,"text":"And that's what I hope my comic strip does in a small way."},{"time":827000,"text":"That's why I like what I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"Thanks for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}